    "instructions":  "1. Preheat oven to 175 degrees Celsius and grease a small loaf pan with cooking spray.\n\n2. In a large bowl, mix the flour, baking powder, salt, and sugar.\n\n3. Pour the beer into the flour mixture.\n\n4. Mix with a wooden spoon and then your hands until well combined; note the batter will be sticky.\n\n5. Pour the batter into the prepared pan.\n\n6. Bake in preheated oven until golden brown on top, about 50-60 minutes.",
